#: ../../../driver-api/media/dtv-core.rst:4
msgid "Digital TV (DVB) devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/dtv-core.rst:6
msgid "Digital TV devices are implemented by several different drivers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/dtv-core.rst:8
msgid ""
"A bridge driver that is responsible to talk with the bus where the other "
"devices are connected (PCI, USB, SPI), bind to the other drivers and "
"implement the digital demux logic (either in software or in hardware);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/dtv-core.rst:12
msgid "Frontend drivers that are usually implemented as two separate drivers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/dtv-core.rst:14
msgid ""
"A tuner driver that implements the logic which commands the part of the "
"hardware responsible for tuning into a digital TV transponder or physical "
"channel. The output of a tuner is usually a baseband or Intermediate "
"Frequency (IF) signal;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/dtv-core.rst:19
msgid ""
"A demodulator driver (a.k.a \"demod\") that implements the logic which "
"commands the digital TV decoding hardware. The output of a demod is a "
"digital stream, with multiple audio, video and data channels typically "
"multiplexed using MPEG Transport Stream [#f1]_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/dtv-core.rst:24
msgid ""
"On most hardware, the frontend drivers talk with the bridge driver using an "
"I2C bus."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/dtv-core.rst:27
msgid ""
"Some standards use TCP/IP for multiplexing data, like DVB-H (an abandoned "
"standard, not used anymore) and ATSC version 3.0 current proposals. "
"Currently, the DVB subsystem doesn't implement those standards."
msgstr ""
